modules.description: This module implements a monadic interface for composing HTTP requests using the `Http_lwt_client`. It provides `get`, `post`, `put`, and `delete` functions for making HTTP calls with custom headers and URLs, returning responses in an `io` monad that supports `map`, `bind`, and error handling via `fail`. The `io` monad sequences operations while encapsulating side effects, enabling precise control over asynchronous HTTP interactions.
